President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Alejandro Mayorkas was nominated for Director of U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services, Department of Homeland Security. Robert O. Blake was nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for South Asian Affairs, Department of State. Jamie M. Morin was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Financial Management, Department of the Air Force, Department of Defense. Thomas R. Lamont was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Army for Manpower and Reserve Affairs, Department of the Army, Department of Defense. Daniel Benjamin was nominated for Coordinator for Counterterrorism, with the rank and status of Ambassador at Large, Department of State. Pearlie S. Reed was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Administration, United States Department of Agriculture. Craig Becker and Mark Pearce were nominated for Board Members of the National Labor Relations Board. President Obama expressed confidence that these individuals would serve with the highest ideals of the nation and looked forward to working with them in the future.